            <section id="overview" class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-globe"></i> International Trading Apps Overview</h2>
                <p>Indian investors can now buy US stocksâ€”Tesla, Nvidia, Apple, Amazonâ€”directly from their smartphones.
                    Thanks to the Liberalized Remittance Scheme (LRS), you can invest up to <strong>$250,000 per
                        financial year</strong> in international markets.</p>
                <p>But which platform should you use? We spent 6 months testing Vested, INDmoney, Groww, ICICI Direct
                    Global, and Interactive Brokers. We opened accounts, transferred money, bought stocks, tested
                    customer support, and analyzed real costs.</p>
                <p>Here's what we found.</p>
                <div class="info-cards-grid">
                    <div class="info-card">
                        <div class="info-card-icon"> <i class="fas fa-rupee-sign"></i> </div>
                        <h4>Zero Commission Era</h4>
                        <p>Vested, INDmoney, and Groww charge â‚¹0 commission on US stock trades. The race to zero is
                            complete.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-card">
                        <div class="info-card-icon"> <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> </div>
                        <h4>LRS Compliance</h4>
                        <p>All platforms handle LRS reporting automatically. You just provide PAN, Aadhaar, and bank
                            account details.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-card">
                        <div class="info-card-icon"> <i class="fas fa-chart-pie"></i> </div>
                        <h4>Fractional Shares</h4>
                        <p>Buy 0.1 shares of Tesla or Nvidia. No need to wait until you have $1,000 for 1 full share.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-card">
                        <div class="info-card-icon"> <i class="fas fa-exchange-alt"></i> </div>
                        <h4>Currency Conversion</h4>
                        <p>Platforms convert INR to USD at real-time rates. Expect 0.5-1% spread above interbank rates.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">What You Need to Get Started</h3>
                <p>To open an international trading account in India, you'll need:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>PAN Card:</strong> Mandatory for LRS compliance and tax reporting.</li>
                    <li><strong>Aadhaar Card:</strong> For KYC verification (Aadhaar-based e-KYC is fastest).</li>
                    <li><strong>Bank Account:</strong> Savings account with a major bank (ICICI, HDFC, SBI, Axis,
                        Kotak).</li>
                    <li><strong>Email & Mobile:</strong> For OTP verification and account alerts.</li>
                    <li><strong>Passport (Optional):</strong> Some platforms (Interactive Brokers) accept passport as
                        alternate ID.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Account opening takes <strong>10-30 minutes</strong> for most platforms. Vested and INDmoney have the
                    fastest onboarding.</p>
            </section>
            <div class="hot-take-box">
                <h4>Contrarian Take</h4>
                <p>Everyone's worried about Meta's metaverse spending. They should be. But what they miss is that Meta's
                    AI advertising engine is so far ahead, they can burn $10B yearly on moonshots and still dominate.
                </p>
            </div>
