            <div class="section-divider"></div> <!-- Section 9: FAQ -->
            <section id="faq" class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-question"></i> Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">1. Which is the best app to buy US stocks from India?</h3>
                <p><strong>For beginners:</strong> Vested Finance (zero commission, excellent research, fractional
                    shares).<br> <strong>For simplicity:</strong> INDmoney (cleanest UI, integrated tax filing).<br>
                    <strong>For advanced traders:</strong> Interactive Brokers (lowest costs at scale, professional
                    tools).</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">2. Is it safe to invest through these apps?</h3>
                <p>Yes. All platforms are LRS-compliant and partner with SEBI-registered or US-registered
                    broker-dealers. Your securities are held in your name and protected by SIPC insurance (up to
                    $500,000 in the US). However, they are not risk-freeâ€”stock market risk applies.</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">3. Can I buy fractional shares of Tesla or Nvidia?</h3>
                <p>Yes, on Vested, INDmoney, Groww, and Interactive Brokers. You can buy as little as 0.01 shares
                    (around â‚¹80-100 for most stocks). ICICI Direct Global doesn't offer fractional shares.</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">4. How much does currency conversion cost?</h3>
                <p>Fintech apps charge 0.5-1% above interbank rates:<br> <strong>Vested:</strong> 0.5-0.75%<br>
                    <strong>INDmoney:</strong> 0.6-0.9%<br> <strong>Groww:</strong> 0.7-1%<br> <strong>Interactive
                        Brokers:</strong> 0.08-0.2% (best rates)<br> <strong>ICICI Direct:</strong> Bank rates
                    (competitive)</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">5. What are the tax implications?</h3>
                <p><strong>Short-term capital gains (STCG):</strong>
                    <24 months, taxed at your income tax slab.<br> <strong>Long-term capital gains (LTCG):</strong> >24
                        months, 20% tax with indexation benefit.<br> <strong>TDS:</strong> 20% TDS deducted at source +
                        4% cess. File ITR to claim credit.<br> <strong>Dividends:</strong> Taxed at your income slab in
                        India (TDS already deducted in US).
                </p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">6. How long does money transfer take?</h3>
                <p><strong>Deposit (INR â†’ USD):</strong> 1-3 business days<br> <strong>Withdrawal (USD â†’ INR):</strong>
                    3-7 business days<br> Vested and INDmoney are the fastest. ICICI Direct can take longer.</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">7. Is there a limit on how much I can invest?</h3>
                <p>Yes, under LRS (Liberalized Remittance Scheme), Indians can remit up to <strong>$250,000 per
                        financial year</strong> for all purposes (including US stock investments). This is per person,
                    per year.</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">8. Can I invest in ETFs like QQQ or SPY?</h3>
                <p>Yes, all platforms offer ETFs. Vested has 200+ ETFs, INDmoney has 300+, Groww has 150+, and
                    Interactive Brokers has access to all US ETFs.</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">9. What happens if the platform shuts down?</h3>
                <p>Your securities are held in your name with the underlying US broker-dealer (DriveWealth for Vested,
                    Interactive Brokers for INDmoney, etc.). If the platform shuts down, you can transfer your holdings
                    to another broker. SIPC insurance protects up to $500,000.</p>
                <h3 class="subsection-title">10. Should I use multiple platforms?</h3>
                <p>Only if you have specific needs. For example:<br> â€¢ Use <strong>Vested</strong> for long-term
                    holdings (research and fractional shares).<br> â€¢ Use <strong>Interactive Brokers</strong> for
                    options trading and large transfers (lower currency fees).<br> Most investors should stick to one
                    platform to avoid complexity.</p>
            </section>
            <div class="section-divider"></div> <!-- Final CTA Section -->
            <section class="article-section">
                <div class="key-takeaways-box" style="text-align: center;">
                    <h3>The Bottom Line</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 20px 0;">For most Indian investors, <strong>Vested
                            Finance</strong> or <strong>INDmoney</strong> are the best choices in 2026. Both offer
                        zero-commission trading, fractional shares, and easy onboarding. Vested wins on research
                        quality, INDmoney wins on UI simplicity.</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 20px 0;">If you're an advanced trader with a large portfolio
                        (>â‚¹10 lakh), <strong>Interactive Brokers</strong> offers the lowest costs at scaleâ€”but prepare
                        for a steep learning curve.</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 20px 0;">If you want the comfort of a traditional bank,
                        <strong>ICICI Direct Global</strong> is reliableâ€”but you'll pay significantly higher fees.</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #C9A227; margin-top: 25px;">Pick your
                        platform. Open an account. Start investing in the US market today.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
